dismissalText.commentary: David Miller not out 130 (133b 11x4 3x6 191m) SR: 97.74
Jean-Paul Duminy c & b Sammy 43 (68b 3x4 0x6 88m) SR: 63.23

dismissalComment.html: drops the length back slightly, slower ball, Duminy through with the shot too soon and chips it back to the bowler! A smart catch reaching out with the right hand and Sammy breaks the partnership. Nice piece of bowling, Duminy deceived, trying to work down the ground and just tapped it back at shoulder height to the bowler

oh boy, what a catch! Another ripper. Du Plessis edges a full delivery, seemed to be aiming leg side, and for a moment Ramdin appears a little wrong-footed but then flings himself low to his right, with one glove, and snaffles the catch. Terrific reflexes.

good length on off stump, Berhardien plays all around it and loses his off stump! It nipped back a little bit but Berhardien was rooted in the crease sort of trying to run it down to third man but missed it by an awful long way and off stump was flattened. Pretty poor innings from Berhardien really

yorker, Parnell trying to flick leg side missed and is bowled! Very nice delivery from Holder, right on line and Parnell played right across it out went middle stump. Again just try and get something on that to get Miller back on strike? Not great cricket from Parnell

steps right across the stumps and goes to scoop over the leg side but finds short long leg! Another wicket falls. Length ball, a cutter, a foot outside off, Phangiso took a big strike to his right and tried to clear the leg side infield but it went straight to the fielder

what a comeback and what a catch! That was the perfect delivery. Full outside off, hint of swing away from the left hander who pushed away from his body. The edge was dying as it headed towards first slip, but Sammy saw it and dived across full length to hold a screamer. Cottrell brings out his salute.

dismissalComment.html: he's done it! Much debate about Behardien's position in the side. Well, he may just have won the match here. A full delivery, nips back a touch and there was a massive gap with Samuels' feet planted on leg stump. Knocks back the leg pole

dismissalText.commentary: Andre Russell not out 64 (40b 5x4 5x6 66m) SR: 160

dismissalComment.html: and it's worked first ball! What a call from de Villiers. Pretty shocking stroke, mind. It's floated up outside off, smartly tempting Gayle, he comes forward to drive but is reaching for the ball and just ends up presenting a catch to cover, neat catch above the head

low full toss, tried to clip it leg side but miscues it a little, taken by midwicket! A fantastic leaping catch with one hand above David Miller's head, a great leap, holds on really well. That should have gone into the stands but Holder was tentative, miscued the leg side flick and couldn't get it over midwicket's head

full, straight, keeps a little low and Ramdin plumb in front! Nipped back a little, Ramdin back on his stumps and the umpire gave it out before the bowler could turn around. Stone dead, back pad, right in front of middle. Poor judgement from Ramdin, it skidded through and that's a plumb as you'll get

dismissalText.commentary: Dwayne Smith b Morkel 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: that's out! It wasn't a contest. Touch fuller, 141kph, pitching around middle, straightens on Smith to beat the outside edge and smashes into middle stump. That is a comprehensive clean-up job. Smith playing an aggressive whip across the line, so didn't give himself the best chance but still a cracking delivery

dismissalText.commentary: Leon Johnson run out (de Villiers/†van Wyk) 18 (40b 2x4 1x6 55m) SR: 45

dismissalComment.html: oh dear, a mix-up costs West Indies. Pushed into the off side off the back foot, Johnson came down for the run but was sent back by Samuels. The throw from cover was swift - from de Villiers - and Johnson's dive wasn't enough. A word, too, for van Wyk who took the ball low by the stumps expertly.

Stone dead, back pad, right in front of middle. Poor judgement from Ramdin, it skidded through and that's a plumb as you'll get

dismissalText.commentary: Jonathan Carter run out (Miller/Duminy) 5 (13b 1x4 0x6 22m) SR: 38.46

dismissalComment.html: played forward into the off side, who wants a single here? Only one of them! The batsmen are at the same end and Carter is run out by a pitch length. That is a shambles. Samuels drove firmly towards mid-off and took three steps down the track, Carter jogged down for the single but Samuels decided it wasn't on so stopped running, selling his partner down the river and there was an easy run out at the bowler's end

dismissalText.commentary: Daren Sammy c de Villiers b Parnell 51 (52b 5x4 2x6 66m) SR: 98.07

dismissalComment.html: the breakthrough, but only just! Sammy carves a full delivery high into the off side, de Villiers runs back from cover, the ball bobbled and he showed brilliant awareness to keep his eyes on it and grasp it as it fell by his chest

dismissalText.commentary: Carlos Brathwaite run out (de Villiers/†van Wyk) 11 (14b 0x4 1x6 23m) SR: 78.57

dismissalComment.html: middle and leg line, dabbed up on the leg side, no single there, Brathwaite sent back but de Villiers is there with the throw and Brathwaite is a long way out! No need for the third umpire. Brathwaite trying to get Russell back on strike but he's too keen and pays the price, nice fielding from de Villiers at midwicket to make up for the dropped catch

commentTextItems.html: full on the stumps and IT'S OUT OF THE GROUND!!! What a victory, what a performance from Andre Russell. Abbott misses his length and Russell does the rest, whacking it way back over long-on!

commentPostTextItems.html: A West Indies victory! Sound the church bells! They still can't turn the series around but another win in the final ODI on Wednesday will see them take some momentum into the World Cup. Join us for that fifth and final ODI at 1.30pm local time on Wednesday, up in Centurion, bye for now...

Something different for the captains to talk about at the presentation. For once AB de Villiers has to explain away a defeat: "It was a good game of cricket. It really hurst to lose. I can't fault the fight we showed. We had some good moments and no so good movements. Andre played exceptionally well. We got tested and it's nice to lose. Great knock by David Miller - great signs for the World Cup. But we bowled some bad balls at the wrong time. We played most of the time but a dropped catch from me and some poor balls gave it away. 22 extras is not nice to know, it's free runs. Sometimes you can try too hard. We showed fighting spirit but a few bad moments gave it away. I'm going to resting for the last game but the lads can take more confidence with a good showing in the last game."

Holder has something to smile at at last: "It means a lot. W've had a tough tour so to get across the line in this game is very special. It was well set up with Darren and Marlon and then Andre was exceptional. The bowlers did an outstanding job with wickets with the new ball and then pressure in the middle overs. I was nervous towards the end but I'm so pleased we got over the line. 262 I would have taken at the start and delighted we got home." Andre Russell takes the Man of the Match for his outstanding finishing job...

West Indies did really well with the ball at the start of the game but then a maiden ODI century from David Miller rescued the innings to give South Africa a competitive total. It looked to be good enough for a long part of the chase but a steady rebuilding job by Samuels and Sammy got the chase going. It ultimately led to a brilliant turnaround from 73 for 5. A victory for Jason Holder, you can't help but be delighted for him.

Finally, we've had a great game and West Indies have got home by one-wicket! A thrilling run chase, set up by Marlon Samuels and Darren Sammy and then finished in superb fashion by Andre Russell whose five sixes have won the match. A brilliant innings and West Indies at last on the board in this series having been hammered in the first three rubbers. Relief and joy for the tourists. A win to saviour here.

commentTextItems.html: great yorker, well dug out back to the bowler, Russell almost falls out of his ground, Abbott throw missed anyway

commentPreTextItems.html: West Indies in touching distance now, what a game. Abbott to try and win it for his side...

commentTextItems.html: length just outside off, steps to leg and carves past backward point! Flies to the boundary, what a shot, great timing, no chance for deep cover, length not the best option from Abbott

full, straighter line, tries to flick leg side and misses, it runs off the pads a short way into the off side, Cottrell is calling a sharp single and Russell is abel to steam up the other end to keep the strike!
oh dear, slips down leg, wide
further outside off, driven powerfully out through cover, what a save by Miller at deep cover! Diving to his left saves four brilliantly
down the track and into the stands again!! Another huge strike over long-on, right to the pitch and bang, six more, fifty for Russell, can he get his side home now?
back in his crease and heaves it over long-on! Big strike. Tad short from the bowler, deep in his crease and hammered away
full length just outside off, driven down to long-off, well played

dismissalText.commentary: Carlos Brathwaite run out (de Villiers/†van Wyk) 11 (14b 0x4 1x6 23m) SR: 78.57

commentTextItems.html: middle and leg line, dabbed up on the leg side, no single there, Brathwaite sent back but de Villiers is there with the throw and Brathwaite is a long way out! No need for the third umpire. Brathwaite trying to get Russell back on strike but he's too keen and pays the price, nice fielding from de Villiers at midwicket to make up for the dropped catch

commentPostTextItems.html: Can Cottrell survive long enough here?

commentTextItems.html: fuller length, swing away again and edged behind! But Russell wants a review. It was given out by Steve Davis. No Hot Spot in this series but we have Real Time Snicko. Russell adamant that there was no edge. No obvious sound on the replay and nothing on RTS too, will this be overturned on this evidence? Yes it is! Russell survives and the match is still alive! Great time to still have the review left

headshotImage.longCaption: Carlos Brathwaite player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: tighter line, Russell tries to step to leg and carve on the off side but is beaten and the ball shaves the off stump too
towards off stump and again it swings alarmingly away and beats the outside edge, this sudden swing is remarkable
too wide of off stump this time, cut at and missed
anther one across Russell and beats him this time, away swing again

length ball sliding across the right-hander, tries to guide to third man and dropped at slip! Bad drop really by de Villiers of all people to his right hand side, he got two hands at shoulder height but it bounced out

commentPreTextItems.html: Still going this chase having threatened to fold several times. Parnell for the 22nd bowling change of the innings...

commentTextItems.html: great bumper, batsman falls on the floor swaying inside the line
dug in around off stump, well played up on his toes knocking this down towards point

commentTextItems.html: well bowled, yorker on leg stump, Russell gets something on it fine of third man, little outside edge looking to turn it to leg I think
slower ball bumper, batsman gets in a pickle and it ends up harmlessly going through to the keeper

dismissalComment.html: steps right across the stumps and goes to scoop over the leg side but finds short long leg! Another wicket falls. Length ball, a cutter, a foot outside off, Phangiso took a big strike to his right and tried to clear the leg side infield but it went straight to the fielder

dismissalText.commentary: Dwayne Smith b Morkel 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: that's out! It wasn't a contest. Touch fuller, 141kph, pitching around middle, straightens on Smith to beat the outside edge and smashes into middle stump. That is a comprehensive clean-up job. Smith playing an aggressive whip across the line, so didn't give himself the best chance but still a cracking delivery

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Gayle c Behardien b Duminy 10 (19b 1x4 0x6 28m) SR: 52.63

dismissalComment.html: and it's worked first ball! What a call from de Villiers. Pretty shocking stroke, mind. It's floated up outside off, smartly tempting Gayle, he comes forward to drive but is reaching for the ball and just ends up presenting a catch to cover, neat catch above the head

headshotImage.longCaption: Morne van Wyk player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Leon Johnson run out (de Villiers/†van Wyk) 18 (40b 2x4 1x6 55m) SR: 45

dismissalComment.html: oh dear, a mix-up costs West Indies. Pushed into the off side off the back foot, Johnson came down for the run but was sent back by Samuels. The throw from cover was swift - from de Villiers - and Johnson's dive wasn't enough. A word, too, for van Wyk who took the ball low by the stumps expertly.

dismissalText.commentary: Marlon Samuels b Behardien 68 (93b 5x4 2x6 146m) SR: 73.11

dismissalComment.html: he's done it! Much debate about Behardien's position in the side. Well, he may just have won the match here. A full delivery, nips back a touch and there was a massive gap with Samuels' feet planted on leg stump. Knocks back the leg pole

dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin lbw b Behardien 3 (5b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: full, straight, keeps a little low and Ramdin plumb in front! Nipped back a little, Ramdin back on his stumps and the umpire gave it out before the bowler could turn around. Stone dead, back pad, right in front of middle. Poor judgement from Ramdin, it skidded through and that's a plumb as you'll get

dismissalText.commentary: Jonathan Carter run out (Miller/Duminy) 5 (13b 1x4 0x6 22m) SR: 38.46

dismissalComment.html: played forward into the off side, who wants a single here? Only one of them! The batsmen are at the same end and Carter is run out by a pitch length. That is a shambles. Samuels drove firmly towards mid-off and took three steps down the track, Carter jogged down for the single but Samuels decided it wasn't on so stopped running, selling his partner down the river and there was an easy run out at the bowler's end

dismissalText.commentary: Daren Sammy c de Villiers b Parnell 51 (52b 5x4 2x6 66m) SR: 98.07

dismissalComment.html: the breakthrough, but only just! Sammy carves a full delivery high into the off side, de Villiers runs back from cover, the ball bobbled and he showed brilliant awareness to keep his eyes on it and grasp it as it fell by his chest

dismissalText.commentary: Andre Russell not out 64 (40b 5x4 5x6 66m) SR: 160
Jason Holder c Miller b Duminy 13 (12b 2x4 0x6 18m) SR: 108.33

dismissalComment.html: low full toss, tried to clip it leg side but miscues it a little, taken by midwicket! A fantastic leaping catch with one hand above David Miller's head, a great leap, holds on really well. That should have gone into the stands but Holder was tentative, miscued the leg side flick and couldn't get it over midwicket's head
